# Agent Must Execute Operations (All Agents – Perpetual)

## CRITICAL: You Do It, Not The User

**You have full SSH capability and terminal access.** NEVER ask the user to run deployment scripts, SSH, tunnel restarts, terminal commands, or debug in a terminal. Execute deploy, Sandbox fix, tunnel restart (cloudflared), and Cloudflare purge yourself using credentials from `.credentials.local`. If deployment or SSH fails, fix the failure and retry; never ask the user to "run this manually" or "fix X" — you fix it.

### What Agents MUST Do Themselves

| Operation | Agent Action | Never |
|-----------|--------------|-------|
| Deploy website to Sandbox | Run deploy script or SSH commands | "Run _deploy_sandbox.py" |
| Deploy MINDEX | Run _deploy_mindex.py (load creds first) | "Set VM_PASSWORD and run..." |
| Deploy MAS | Run rebuild script or SSH | "SSH to 188 and run..." |
| Start dev server | ALWAYS launch externally with -WindowStyle Hidden (no pop-up): Start-Process powershell -WindowStyle Hidden ... npm run dev:next-only; NEVER in Cursor | NEVER run inside Cursor — uses too much memory |
| Free port 3010 | Run Stop-Process / taskkill | "Run this in admin PowerShell" |
| Purge Cloudflare | Run purge API (_cloudflare_cache.py or curl) | "Go to Cloudflare and purge" |
| NAS assets / videos | Upload directly to NAS via UniFi web UI | **NEVER** run `_sync_nas_push_from_windows.py` — it destroys NAS and local videos (0-byte overwrites) |
| Health checks | Run curl / Invoke-WebRequest | "Check if it's running" |
| Browser verification | Use cursor-ide-browser MCP to test pages | "Test in your browser" |
| Kill stale processes | Run dev-machine-cleanup.ps1 | "Run the cleanup script" |
| SSH to VMs (187/188/189) | Use paramiko/plink with creds from .credentials.local | "SSH to the VM and run..." |
| **Proxmox** (onboot, start VM, vzdump/cron on host) | Run `python scripts/proxmox/apply_production_vm_policy_api.py` after loading creds; API token + optional root SSH to PVE. See `proxmox-agents-execute-all.mdc`. | "Open Proxmox UI…" / "SSH to Proxmox…" |
| Restart Sandbox tunnel (1033) | Run _restart_sandbox_tunnel.py or SSH + sudo systemctl restart cloudflared | "Restart cloudflared on 187" |

### Scripts That Must NEVER Exist or Run

- **`_sync_nas_push_from_windows.py`** — DELETED. It caused catastrophic data loss (0-byte overwrites of NAS and local videos). Do not recreate it. To add videos: upload directly to the NAS via UniFi web UI; the VM mounts the NAS.

### Credentials

Credentials are in `.credentials.local` (MAS repo root). Load them before deploy/SSH:

```powershell
Get-Content "C:\Users\admin2\Desktop\MYCOSOFT\CODE\MAS\mycosoft-mas\.credentials.local" | ForEach-Object {
  if ($_ -match "^([^#=]+)=(.*)$") { [Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable($matches[1].Trim(), $matches[2].Trim(), "Process") }
}
```

Then run deploy scripts—they use `$env:VM_PASSWORD` or `$env:VM_SSH_PASSWORD`.

### Protocol

1. **When deployment is needed:** Load credentials, run the deploy script or SSH commands.
2. **When dev server is needed:** Check port 3010; if stuck, kill process; then **start the dev server with Start-Process powershell -WindowStyle Hidden ...** so it runs externally with no window pop-up. See run-servers-externally.mdc.
3. **When something fails:** Run diagnostic commands yourself; fix or report with specifics.
4. **If a command needs elevation:** Try alternatives (taskkill, different approach) before mentioning elevation.

### Remember

The user will **never** run deployment, NAS sync, Cloudflare purge, or debugging when you can do it. You are the operator. Sub-agents (deploy-pipeline, infrastructure-ops, etc.) exist to do this work—invoke them. If something fails, fix it and retry. Never hand work back to the user.
